In 2013, American recording artist [[Marc Anthony]] covered "Flor Pálida" on his album ''[[3.0 (Marc Anthony album)|3.0]]''. Released as the third single from the album,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.elnuevodia.com/marcanthonyencabezalaportadaderevistadeejercicios-1773700.html|title=Marc Anthony encabeza la portada de revista de ejercicios
|work=[[El Nuevo Dia]]}}</ref> Anthony's cover was arranged and produced by American musician [[Sergio George]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/30-mw0002550345|title=3.0 - Marc Anthony|publisher=AllMusic. Prometheus Global Media}}</ref> Hector Aviles from Latino Music Cafe called Anthony's cover "a great tribute to Polo’s original version with his performance."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latinomusiccafe.com/2013/08/19/latin-music-album-marc-anthonys-3-0-review/|title=Latin Music Album: Marc Anthony’s 3.0 Review|last=Aviles|first=Hector|publisher=Latin Music Cafe|date=August 19, 2013|accessdate=April 28, 2014}}</ref> [[New York Times]] editor Ben Ratliff referred "Flor Pálida" along with "Espera" and "Cautivo de Este Amor" as the "best of the kind".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/07/23/arts/music/marc-anthony-returns-to-salsa-chris-morrissey-crosses-lines.html|title=Marc Anthony Returns to Salsa; Chris Morrissey Crosses Lines|last=Ratliff|first=Ben|work=[[New York Times]]|publisher=[[New York Times Company]]|date=July 22, 2013|accessdate=April 28, 2014}}</ref> A.D. Amorosi of the ''[[Philadelphia Inquirer]]'' called the song "impresionante".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.northjersey.com/arts-and-entertainment/music/music-reviews-robin-thicke-backstreet-boys-marc-anthony-1.631873?page=all|title=Music reviews: Robin Thicke, Backstreet Boys, Marc Anthony|author=A.D. Amorosi|work=[[Philadelphia Inquirer]]|publisher=northjersey.com|date=August 6, 2013|accessdate=April 28, 2014}}</ref>

